==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Columbella
<hw>Col`um*bel"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., dim.
of L. <ets>columba</ets> a dove. So called from a fancied resemblance in
color and form, of some species.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus
of univalve shells, abundant in tropical seas. Some species, as
<spn>Columbella mercatoria</spn>, were formerly used as shell
money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Columbia</ent>⟦br⟧
